/*

Function Objects vs Function Pointers

    When to Use What?

    Use Case	                   Function Pointers	 Function Objects
    Simple callbacks	               ✅ Yes	        🔸 Not necessary
    Maintaining state	               ❌ No              ✅ Yes
    Used in STL algorithms	           ❌ No	             ✅ Yes
    Efficient execution	               ✅ Yes (faster)	🔸 Slightly slower



//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

 To see he assembly file from C++ code

    step 1:

    Build c++ project from vs code.
    main.s file will be generated in build dir.

    ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
    step 2:

    In the assembly file:

    Look for functions with mangled names. 
    Use c++filt to demangle names for better readability.

    _Z3addIiET_S0_S0_:     # Template instantiated for int
    _Z3addIdET_S0_S0_:     # Template instantiated for double

    To demangle:

    $c++filt _Z3addIiET_S0_S0_

    output:
    add<int>(int, int)
    
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

*/